 Technical (wasting very little while working or producing something) for each farm is calculated 
 as TE = Y /Ymax = exp( T ), where the guess of T 
 is received/got from (6). This measure of technical 
 (wasting very little while working or producing something) is called output increasing since it 
 hints that actual output is below the edge of something/unexplored area 
 output by [1 - exp( T )]_) X 100%. Or, output could be increased by [1 - exp( T )]_) X 100% if 
 the farm becomes technically (producing a lot with very little waste). The frequency distribution of TE is reported in Table 2. 
 None of the farms in the sample is fully technically (producing a lot with very little waste). The mean (wasting very little while working or producing something) of these farms 
 is 75.46%; the maximum is 85.87% and the smallest 55.45%. So, possible output of these 
 farms, given their input usage, is much higher. 
 
