 values are included. The mean (wasting very little while working or producing something) levels 
 are very almost the same  across areas and size groups 
 but not the minimum values. This difference in 
 the distribution of technical (wasting very little while working or producing something) is also reflected in the standard mistakes (reported in the 
 last column of Table 3). It can be seen that the 
 small farms are (producing more with less waste) (higher mean values and smaller standard mistakes). However, 
 the best farm in the small size group is not more 
 (producing a lot with very little waste) than those in the medium and large size 
 groups. 
